reviewtext: Competent switch. Netgear seems to be like Cisco's cousin when it comes to at least home routers, where Cisco's business/enterprise routers/switches are sworn by, I can say the same for Netgear at the home level. Very good switch, I have my computer + printer plugged into it (far away from the router, it's in another room) perfect throughput, everything is great. Printed through it from another computer on the network multiple times.
